= SDL_GL_SwapWindow =
Use this function to update a window with OpenGL rendering.


== Syntax ==
```c++
void SDL_GL_SwapWindow(SDL_Window* window)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''window'''
|the window to change
|}

== Code Examples ==
```c++
You can add your code example here
```

== Remarks ==
This is used with double-buffered OpenGL contexts, which are the default.

On OS X make sure you bind 0 to the draw framebuffer before swapping the window, otherwise nothing will happen. See [http://renderingpipeline.com/2012/05/nsopenglcontext-flushbuffer-might-not-do-what-you-think/ this blog post] for more info.

